[div class=p 
	""Standard" 
	(__wikiLink|href=/Class|implicitdisplaytext=class)
	" publications are the vast majority of runs on TASVideos.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Current publications|href=/Movies-Standard)
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Obsoleted publications|href=/Movies-Standard-Obsonly)
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h3 id=Overview 
	" Overview
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" Aims to fulfill the site's goal of being a Tool-Assisted Speedrun records site, as well as be an information based central repository for the body of TAS literature.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Applicable Movie Rules|href=/MovieRules#Standard)
		".
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h3 id=TechnicalRequirements 
	" Technical requirements
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" Must beat all known records, including other TASes.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Must show a proficient understanding of TAS techniques and be perceived as well optimized: It should not have obvious pauses, mistakes, or sloppy play.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" If starting from a premade save file, a verification movie producing that save file is required.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h3 id=AcceptableGoals 
	" Acceptable goals
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"All these goals can be published as separate branches.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			"Completion Percentage
		]b
		" goals:
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" 
				(__wikiLink|displaytext=Fastest Completion|href=/LegacyPages/FastestCompletion)
				" (often called "any%") - Fastest completion of a game using all available options, including major skip glitches (save/memory corruption, arbitrary code execution, etc).
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" 
				(__wikiLink|displaytext=Full Completion|href=/MovieTagGuidelines#100Completion)
				" - Fastest completion of 
				[em 
					"all
				]em
				" content in the game without glitching the completion statistics.
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" 
				(__wikiLink|displaytext=Lowest Completion|href=/MovieTagGuidelines#LowCompletion)
				" - Fastest completion of the 
				[em 
					"least
				]em
				" content in the game without glitching the completion statistics.
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			(__wikiLink|displaytext=Forgoes Major Skip Glitch|href=/MovieTagGuidelines#ForgoesMajorSkipGlitch)
		]b
		" - Avoids major skips or the glitches that lead to them but otherwise aims for fastest completion.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			(__wikiLink|displaytext=Multiplayer|href=/MovieTagGuidelines#NumberOfCharacters)
		]b
		" goals - For games where you can control several character at once, up to 3 branches are allowed:
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" Minimum players (usually 1)
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" Maximum players (usually 2)
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" Some other player count if it's faster than both of the above
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			"Difficulty
		]b
		" goals - For games with several difficulty settings, we allow up to 3 branches to co-exist:
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" 
				(__wikiLink|displaytext=Easiest|href=/MovieTagGuidelines#UsesEasiestDifficulty)
				" difficulty
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" 
				(__wikiLink|displaytext=Hardest|href=/MovieTagGuidelines#UsesHardestDifficulty)
				" difficulty
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" Any other setting if it's faster than both of the above
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			(__wikiLink|displaytext=Score Attack|href=/MovieTagGuidelines#AimsForMaximumScore)
		]b
		" - Highest attainable score in-game, barring infinite scoring loops.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			(__wikiLink|displaytext=In-Game Codes|href=/MovieTagGuidelines#UsesAnInGameCode)
		]b
		" - Same as "Fastest Completion", but also allows 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=in-game codes|href=/Glossary#CodeModification)
		" that add gameplay or in-game mechanics.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			(__wikiLink|displaytext=Savegame|href=/MovieTagGuidelines#StartsFromASavedStateOrSram)
		]b
		" - Game modes that are 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=locked behind game completion|href=/Glossary#SaveRam)
		", or categories that benefit from 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=New Game+|href=/Glossary#NewGamePlus)
		" carryover.
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" SaveRAM runs are branched separately from any Power-On counterparts.
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			"Glitchless
		]b
		" - Completing the game as fast as possible while avoiding all known glitches (defined per game in accordance with the community).
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Additional goals are under consideration and will be implemented incrementally.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h3 id=GoalsCurrentlyUnderConsideration 
	" Goals currently under consideration
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			"Warps
		]b
		" - Fastest completion using intended warps or shortcuts. If major skip glitches are available in the game, avoiding them is allowed for this category.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			"Warpless
		]b
		" - Fastest completion without using intended shortcuts.
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" This includes branches such as "all levels".
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" More standard goals will be added in the future based on community feedback.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h3 id=Entertainment 
	" Entertainment 
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" Entertainment is always encouraged, though unnecessary, and will not affect the judgement of a run that otherwise qualifies.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Speed/entertainment tradeoffs are allowed.
	]li
]ul
